With regard to the typology of the mobile market in the Czech Republic, it is obvious that the entry of another competitor would put on him and above all his high claims."
However, the attitude of mobile telephony operators is quite surprising the complete disinterest of the Czech regulators.
This is not just the attitude of the CTU which unfortunately in the Czech Republic - unlike Britain and other developed countries - has no power to interfere in economic competition.
It belongs exclusively to the Office for the Protection of Economic Competition (UOHS).
This, however, in relation to the whole problem has taken its typical position.
"The entry of the virtual operator into the mobile phone market would be possible after the conclusion of the contract of rental of the necessary infrastructure between a mobile operator and a virtual operator has been realized.
No such contract has been concluded so far because the offer of potential buyers probably wasn't interesting enough for traditional operators," said Kristian Chalupa, the section for external relations ÚOHS, in response to our questionnaire.
